CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 26, 1965, pg. 8, reads: "SWEEPSTAKES WINNER - Mrs. Eleanor Campbell, a nursery school teacher of Grotto St., was a "Sight-Seeing Sweepstakes" winner in Sherman Shoes contest. She won a large "carry" bag which holds six pairs of shoes, and two pairs of Joyce Shoes.  Mrs. Dorothy Zeafel Brown (left), assistant treasurer of the East Liberty Chamber of Commerce, presented the gift to Mrs. Campbell, while Perry L. Sherman of Sherman Shoes, on Penn Ave., looks on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Dorothy Zeafel Brown, on left, and Perry L. Sherman presenting floral Atlantic bag to sweepstakes winner Eleanor Campbell, in Sherman Shoes store, Penn Avenue, East Liberty
